                <h1>Enhance Background Noise in Your Recordings: A Simple Guide</h1>
                <p>To enhance background noise in a recording, use audio editing software such as Audacity or Adobe Audition. Start by isolating the desired background sound using filters or equalizers. Increase volume and adjust levels for balance. Consider using compression to smooth variations, and add reverb for depth. Export settings should maintain audio fidelity.</p>
